## 19. Code Quality Standards

All code in this repository MUST meet the following standards before being merged or released.

### 19.1 Code Formatting — Black

- All Python source files MUST be formatted with `black`
- In CI, black MUST be run with `--check`; any file that would be reformatted MUST fail the pipeline
- Black configuration MUST be defined in `pyproject.toml`

### 19.2 Linting — Flake8

- All Python source files MUST pass `flake8` with zero violations
- Flake8 configuration MUST be stored in `.flake8` in the repository root
- The maximum line length SHOULD be consistent with the black configuration (typically 88 characters)

### 19.3 Testing — pytest

- All functionality MUST have corresponding unit tests under the `tests/` directory
- Tests MUST be runnable with `pytest` from the repository root
- Test coverage MUST be measured with branch coverage enabled and MUST not fall below **80%**
- Coverage reports MUST be generated in `term-missing` format (for CI logs) and `xml` format (for SonarCloud)
- The pipeline MUST fail if coverage falls below the threshold

### 19.4 Coverage Configuration

A `.coveragerc` file MUST be present and MUST include at minimum:

```ini
[run]
branch = True
source = src

[report]
fail_under = 80
```

