## 22. Compliance Checklist

Before publishing an image or merging to `main`, the following MUST be verified:

### Container
- [ ] Base image pinned to Python 3.10+, non-`latest` tag using `-slim` variant
- [ ] `PYTHONUNBUFFERED` and `PYTHONDONTWRITEBYTECODE` set in Dockerfile
- [ ] All runtime dependencies in `requirements.txt` pinned to exact versions including `boto3` and `pyyaml`
- [ ] `pip` upgraded before dependency installation; `--no-cache-dir` used throughout
- [ ] `requirements.txt` installed before application code is copied
- [ ] Non-root user created and active before `ENTRYPOINT`
- [ ] No credentials or secrets present in the image
- [ ] `ENTRYPOINT` uses exec form; `CMD` defaults to `--help`
- [ ] `.dockerignore` present and excludes `tests/`, `requirements-dev.txt`, caches, and VCS files
- [ ] Image tagged with a semantic version

### Application
- [ ] `start` command accepts `--tag-key` and `--tag-value`; no `--asg-name` argument exists
- [ ] `start` writes `INSTANCE_REFRESH_ID=<id>` to `outputs/refresh.env` in dotenv format
- [ ] `outputs/` directory auto-created if absent; no error if already exists
- [ ] `SkipMatching` defaults to `true` in all `StartInstanceRefresh` API calls
- [ ] `--no-skip-matching` sets `SkipMatching` to `false`
- [ ] `--max-healthy-percentage` constrained to 100–200 and validated against `--min-healthy-percentage`
- [ ] `monitor` reads refresh ID from `outputs/refresh.env` when `--refresh-id` is not provided
- [ ] `monitor` exits with correct code for all terminal AWS states and local conditions
- [ ] Tag lookup handles zero, one, and multiple matches with correct exit codes
- [ ] Tag matching is case-sensitive
- [ ] All exit codes defined and consistently applied

### Configuration
- [ ] `config/config.yaml` present with all required keys and correct defaults
- [ ] `config/config.example.yaml` present with all keys documented
- [ ] CLI arguments take precedence over config file values
- [ ] `artifacts.output_dir` and `artifacts.refresh_env_filename` configurable

### IAM
- [ ] Minimum IAM policy documented (`StartInstanceRefresh`, `DescribeInstanceRefreshes`, `DescribeAutoScalingGroups`)
- [ ] No credentials in image, config files, or repository

### Code Quality
- [ ] `requirements-dev.txt` present with `black`, `flake8`, `pytest`, `pytest-cov` pinned
- [ ] `.flake8` present and consistent with black line length
- [ ] `.coveragerc` present with `branch = True` and `fail_under = 80`
- [ ] All tests pass; coverage ≥ 80% with branch coverage enabled
- [ ] No black formatting violations
- [ ] No flake8 violations

### Pipeline
- [ ] All required CI/CD secret variables documented and configured in GitLab
- [ ] `sonar-project.properties` present with all required keys including `sonar.qualitygate.wait=true`
- [ ] `.releaserc.json` present with correct branch and plugin configuration
- [ ] `sonarcloud` and `semgrep` run in parallel in the `analysis` stage
- [ ] `start-refresh` publishes `outputs/refresh.env` as a `dotenv` report artifact
- [ ] `monitor-refresh` declares `needs` with `artifacts: true` from `start-refresh`
- [ ] `release` stage depends on `monitor-refresh` and only runs on `main`
- [ ] Conventional commit format enforced; version bump table documented
